From http://www.discogs.com/artist/Half+Eye:

Taking the stage fright cue directly from Andy Partridge, Half Eye began recording in 1991 as an indie rock serenade to German cult actor Udo Kier. A host of DIY releases, reluctant performances, lineups and locales later, Half Eye v. 2008 is on the verge of replacing Robert Pollard as prolific\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&#039;s poster boy with a lineup including Hank Baker (The Miss, The Brogues), Travis Doane (The Gordon Taylor) and Nate Wright (Coho). Half Eye maintains most of its members in the Pacific Northwest of the US.
